features: Protect your child's hearing: TuneFlux kids headphones are designed with a volume limiter of 85dB, preventing hearing damage caused by prolonged exposure to high decibel sound. They are incredibly lightweight, which makes them an excellent option for toddlers and younger kids.
Enjoy immersive audio: With large 40mm dynamic sound generating units, TuneFlux kids headphones deliver powerful treble and rich bass audio for an authentic listening experience.

Comfortable for all-day wear: The protein leather ear cups and memory foam lining on these headphones provide a soft and comfortable fit, while the retractable headband adjusts to fit your child's head size. Plus, the design is elastic enough to avoid pinching the ear, even during long listening sessions.

Built to last: Made from super impact-resistant ABS plastic and durable wires, TuneFlux kids headphones can withstand unintentional pulling and tearing during playtime. Plus, they come with a 2-year warranty for added peace of mind.
Stylish and fun to wear: Choose from 4 different colorways to find the perfect match for your child's style. TuneFlux kids headphones are cute, stylish, and practical.

Perfect Gift Choice Tuneflux kids headphones make a perfect gift for little ones. They're stylish, comfortable, and come in fun, vibrant colors. Customer-first Approach At TuneFlux, we pride ourselves on providing exceptional customer experiences. We take every question or concern seriously and work hard to ensure our customers are satisfied. You can trust us to go above and beyond to make sure you have a positive experience with our products.

Hearing Protection Tuneflux toddler headphones limit the volume to 85dB, protecting children's ears from potential damage caused by loud sounds. In fact, they have been tested to withstand tens of thousands of plug and unplug cycles, ensuring long-lasting durability. Egonomic kids Design Tuneflux kids' headphones are designed with a perfect size and fit for children, ensuring long-lasting comfort during extended use. Adjustable Headband The kids lightweight headphones can be easily adjusted to achieve a perfect fit and long-lasting comfort for your child, especially suitable for children aged 1-5.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great first-pair of headphones!
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my 18 month old's first plane ride. The volume has a limit, so I felt safe with him using them without it being too loud. They were a little big on him still, but they were adjustable and they worked - and will work as he grows. Having a wire is an inconvenience, but this one was nice and long so it wasn't too bad.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great kids headphones
reviews.reviewText: I ordered these headphone for my 1st grader. They were a great price and came in her favorite color purple which was a bonus. She uses these at school (they don’t come home) and she says that they are working good. Her previous pair of headphone that we had gotten at target for more money had broken/weren’t working right st school. I was happy with the way these looked. They have nice plush cushions over the ear and seem pretty durable so we shall see, but so far no complaints here.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars great quality headphone, with sound controlled and suitable for my toddler
reviews.reviewText: Ordered this as a gift for my toddler, the quality is very good for the price, attractive color (I ordered the pink one) the earpiece has nice soft padding and is overall pretty sturdy....and she is liking it very much...With respect to size, this headphone is well designed for the small head circumference, with regards to volume, its appropriate for delicate ears and the cord is perfect in length. Overall very satisfied with the look and made of the product. Shipping was prompt and was delivered in good packaging.

reviews.reviewText: Bought these for my kids for school and they work well. The only complaint from my kids is the size of the ear spot, one has been complaining it feels tight on his ear.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for a child
reviews.reviewText: I bought these headphones because my 2 yo daughter always wanted to wear my headphones, but they are way too big. These are sized perfectly but can also be adjusted bigger. They are decent quality for the price, but I won’t be out a lot of money if they do break. These headphones don’t have any volume control on them and are corded only, but that’s what I wanted. My daughter is happy to have her own headphones now.
